Since `G` is binomial random, the presence of edges is independent. So, `P(e₁ ∈ G ω) = p` and `P(e₂ ∈ G ω) = p`. Then `P(e₁ ∈ G ω ∧ e₂ ∈ G ω) = p * p = p²`.

